<item>
            <title>[HBASE-3648] [replication] failover is sloppy with znodes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3648</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;ReplicationZookeeper is a bit sloppy in how it handles the znodes during failover:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;when creating the lock, it doesn&apos;t cleanly handle the situation where the parent znode might already be deleted.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;when deleting the znodes after a successful move, it doesn&apos;t make sure to delete the lock znode last.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;after deleting the lock, there&apos;s a window where another region server could have already created another lock and deleted the znodes which would abort the first region server (saw it on one cluster).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12501494">HBASE-3648</key>
